# Optiweb Usage Examples

This file contains usage examples for the Optiweb CLI tool.

## Basic Usage

To optimize your images with the default settings:

```bash
optiweb --input ./images --output ./optimized
```

This command optimizes all JPG and PNG files in the "images" folder and saves them to the "optimized" folder.

## WebP Conversion

To convert your images to WebP format:

```bash
optiweb --input ./images --output ./optimized --webp
```

This command optimizes and converts all JPG and PNG files to WebP format.

## Adjusting Quality

To set the quality of optimized images:

```bash
optiweb --input ./images --output ./optimized --quality 90
```

The quality value must be between 0 and 100. The default is 85.

## Skip Existing Files

To skip files that already exist in the output folder:

```bash
optiweb --input ./images --output ./optimized --skip-existing
```

## Verbose Output

To get more detailed output:

```bash
optiweb --input ./images --output ./optimized --verbose
```

## Full Example

A full example using multiple parameters:

```bash
optiweb --input ./images --output ./optimized --webp --quality 85 --skip-existing --verbose
```
